Justice Ismaila Abdullahi of an Upper Area Court in Abuja has revoked the bail of a popular aphrodisiac seller, Hauwa Mohammed aka Jaruma. Delivering judgment on Wednesday, the judge ordered the re-arrest of Jaruma. He directed that she should be remanded in the Suleja Correctional Centre following her and lawyers’ absence in court. Abdullahi, therefore, adjourned the case to March 17, 2022. DAILY POST recalls that Jaruma was granted bail after she was arraigned before an Upper Area Court for alleged defamation of character, false news publication and intimidation of actress Regina Daniels’ husband, Ned Nwoko, on Instagram. 